The paper discusses the effect of log-likelihood ratio saturation on belief propagation decoder low-density parity-check codes, which is a topic related to information theory (cs.IT). The analysis also involves the stability of density evolution, which is a topic related to networked systems (cs.NI) and social networks (cs.SI). The paper also discusses the threshold analysis, which is a topic related to distributed systems (cs.DS) and computational complexity (cs.CC).
